# Agent workflow (ship loop)

Adapted from [gm](https://anentrypoint.github.io/gm/) — lightweight, not a replacement for project rules.

## PLAN (before coding)

- Confirm scope in one sentence; one feature or fix per change.
- Read `DEV.md` for player flows; read `.cursor/skills/gigazonk-development/SKILL.md` for architecture.
- Identify files, save migration need, and which test gates apply (see `browser-game-testing.mdc`).

## EXECUTE

- Data/constants → manager/module → thin `Game.js` wiring.
- Run commands in the terminal; do not only print them.
- Minimal diff; match surrounding style; no drive-by refactors.

## VERIFY (before saying "done")

| Change type | Minimum gate |
|-------------|--------------|
| Docs only | None |
| Logic / data | `npm run check` |
| UI / HUD / menus | `check` + `test:e2e:headed` or `:ui` |
| Pre-PR / user asked to ship | `check` + `test:e2e`; add `test:e2e:cross` if UI/e2e touched |

Fix failures before reporting complete. Summarize what ran and pass counts.

## EMIT (commit / PR)

- **Only when the user explicitly asks** to commit or open a PR.
- Commit message: `type(scope): why` — imperative, one logical change.
- PR via `gh`; never force-push `main`.
- Structural changes: update `ARCHITECTURE.md`, sync wiki, commit `wiki/**` (see `ship-quality.mdc`).

## COMPLETE

- Player-visible feature → note manual playtest URL (`http://localhost:5173/?dev=1`).
- Meta/save changes → confirm `GAME_VERSION` + migration in `SaveData.js`.
- Do not merge PRs unless the user asks.
